name: D. Scott Phoenix
title: Ex founder + CEO of Vicarious AI (raised $250M, acq by Alphabet). Partner at @fiftyyears investing in hard tech. Twitter: @fuelfive
about:
Partner at Fifty Years, investing in deep tech founders at the earliest stages. More about me: https://dscottphoenix.com

Previously, I was cofounder and CEO of Vicarious, an AGI and robotics startup backed by ~$250M from Dustin Moskovitz, Mark Zuckerberg, Elon Musk, Jeff Bezos, Founders Fund, Khosla Ventures, DCVC, 8VC, and many others. At Vicarious, I worked with my cofounder Dileep George and our talented team to build one of the first successful AI + robotics companies, as well as publish peer-reviewed research in Science, NeurIPS, ICML, and more. 

Vicarious was acquired by Alphabet in 2022. After the acquisition, I spent a year as the Chief Product & Revenue Officer of Intrinsic, Alphabet’s “other bet” focused on robotics and AI.

Before Vicarious, I was an entrepreneur in residence at Founders Fund, started a company in the Y Combinator 2008 batch, and built an open source game. I also invest in hard tech startups like Sila Nano, Psi Quantum, Verge Genomics, and Science, and advise venture funds like Felicis Ventures, Base10, and 8VC.

name: Matthew Zeiler
title: Founder & CEO at Clarifai | Pioneering the full stack AI platform
about:
I founded Clarifai in 2013 shortly after completing my PhD at New York University. Before that, I had the privilege of working alongside renowned machine learning pioneers Geoff Hinton, Rob Fergus, Yann LeCun, and Jeff Dean. This experience really cultivated my passion for deep learning which is the foundation for all the AI we do at Clarifai.

Today, I work with some of the most brilliant people in the industry in order to simplify the complexities of getting AI into production for organizations. We have built the full stack AI platform having all the tools you need in one place for data labelling, data management, training and evaluation of models, elastic model inference, model monitoring, active learning, streamlit UI modules, and much more. Collectively this streamlines for our customers their procurement, legal/security review, and development/maintenance when applying AI to production use cases. Join us on our mission to Empower developers to quickly co-create, share, and use The World AI(TM) in production.

name: Olcan Sercinoglu

about:
I'm also on Twitter: @olcan (https://twitter.com/olcan)
We are hiring! Learn more at https://scaledinference.com/careers 
Below is my bio copied from https://scaledinference.com/our-team

Before founding Scaled Inference, Olcan was an engineer in Google Brain, where he worked on efficient inference methods for general-purpose statistical models and task-specific adaptations that can utilize deep learning. Early on at Google Olcan led several core platform projects that now power virtually all major Google services including Web Search. He later developed the on-demand statistical analysis system that powers Google Trends and subsequently spent many years working on web-scale statistical inference systems at Google Research while also studying AI at Stanford (MS) and UC Berkeley (PhD). Prior to joining Google, Olcan built a popular (10M+ pageviews/month) music search engine and a web analytics platform as side projects during his undergraduate studies at Washington University in St. Louis, where he graduated valedictorian with a BS in Computer Science. Olcan is also an avid tennis player who rates himself “a solid 4.0-4.5” on the NTRP scale.

name: Alex Poon
title: CEO & Founder, MadScript - Elite personal branding for scrappy founders.
location: New York, New York, United States
about:
When I was building x.ai, I led the team that pushed my cofounder’s LinkedIn profile to 500k followers. This helped us build a 100k waitlist for our AI agent, convert top VCs and entrepreneurs into users, and raise $40M+. In my last venture, when we shipped the Scout Game protocol, we launched with thousands of initial users and partnered with some of the largest web3 ecosystems. This was primarily thanks to my cofounder’s 100k+ Farcaster followers.

I’ve seen the impact firsthand and know the tools and tricks. Yet, I’ve never consistently approached personal branding myself. Whenever I tried to take it seriously, running the business always pulled me away. The second the next product release, sales call, VC meeting, or HR crisis needed me, I dropped content creation and social engagements.

I built MadScript for me.... and for you.

name: Dan Starr
title: ML Platform Engineer, Data Scientist, former Co-founder at wise.io
about:
Data scientist and ML platform engineer with experience spanning academic research and startup founding, specializing in productionizing machine learning and analytics solutions across diverse domains—from astronomy to industrial sensor data, automotive, farm and customer support automation. I bridge the gap between innovative ML applications and cost-efficient cloud operations.

At Aquabyte, I develop and productionize ML pipelines, lead cloud platform management, and oversee infrastructure that has reduced compute and storage costs by roughly 60%. I also manage observability, uptime, and incident response for products and services supporting dozens of models and telemetry streams from hundreds of stereoscopic edge devices, and I have identified business processes that can be improved with ML, then developed and productionized ML models that enhance customer support and device issue identification.

Before joining Aquabyte, I co-developed an ML framework for consulting projects and co-founded an enterprise ML startup later acquired by GE Digital, where I held roles spanning data science, data engineering, observability, CloudOps/DevOps.

My expertise lies in building productionized ML and analytics applications with clear KPI observability. I have developed a robust framework for this purpose and continue to refine it across diverse projects.

I am also deeply interested in applying ML and analytics to temporal data. My career began with real-time time-series challenges in astronomy, evolved into automotive and industrial sensor applications, and expanded into CloudOps and MLOps. Recently, I have focused on IoT sensors, aggregating data and APIs to develop models for both image and time-series datasets.

name: Sanjay Dhawan
title: CEO of SymphonyAI
about:
I’m a results-driven technology veteran and serial entrepreneur with a proven track record of improving operational and organizational success for multi-billion-dollar businesses. With over three decades of leadership experience in the technology space, I have a deep understanding of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) applications, with specific expertise developing solutions at the intersection of devices, sensors, cloud solutions and data integration. 

In January, 2022, I started as CEO of SymphonyAI, a leader in high-value enterprise AI software solutions for strategic industries, including retail, consumer packaged goods, financial services, manufacturing, media, and IT operations. Founded in 2017, SymphonyAI has nearly 2,000 employees and is backed by a $1 billion commitment by entrepreneur Dr. Romesh Wadhwani.

Previously, I served as the President and CEO of Cerence Inc., the premier provider of A.I.-powered assistants and innovations for connected and autonomous vehicles and across the mobility ecosystem. In this role, I was responsible for Cerence’s day-to-day operations and financial performance, which has 60+ automotive customers and whose technology can be found in more than 350 million vehicles globally. 

I previously spent nearly a decade at HARMAN, where I served as both the President and CEO of the company’s Symphony Teleca division, as well as President of HARMAN Connected Services. During my time there, I developed the strategy and roadmap for the company’s Connected Life initiative that transforms digital experiences across automotive, consumer, and enterprise markets. I was in a unique position at HARMAN, working with Cerence (formerly Nuance Automotive) as both a partner and a customer.

I’ve also authored several networking-related publications and books and have chaired IEEE 802 and ANSI X3T9 standards sub-groups. I received my master’s degree in Electrical Engineering from Brunel University, England, and my bachelor’s degree in Electronics and Communications from REC Kurukshetra, India.
notable_achievements: CEO of Cerence Inc; Significant insider trading activity with Cerence Inc and HARMAN International Industries
reasoning: Sanjay Dhawan demonstrates a strong track record as a senior executive and innovator in the technology sector, particularly in AI and connected technologies. He has led multiple billion-dollar businesses, including Cerence (public company) and major divisions of HARMAN. His role in transforming digital experiences across automotive and enterprise markets, combined with his technical contributions (IEEE standards, publications) and current leadership of SymphonyAI (2000 employees, $1B backing) places him firmly in the Market Innovator category. name: Nikos Tzagkarakis
title:
Founder at Collective Intelligence & Fellow (Cohort 8) at Edmund Hillary Fellowship (EHF),
Published Author of "As It Turns Out, No Ones Got Their Shit Together",
Podcast: Stuff that matters now
about:
I first became a company director 25 years ago. Since then, I have had experience on a number of boards, both private and public, and have become fascinated in the evolutionary journey of professionals.
What I’ve observed is that some develop, yet many, after a burst of success, stagnate then diminish with time.
It’s why I’ve become fascinated with the challenge of - how do we keep our people evolving, in a world that continues to change?
As a director, we would send senior staff off to courses yet no meaningful change would occur – very frustrating and a waste of investment.
So…… I drew on my farming background and remodeled the farm discussion group, which is a key catalyst to technical transfer in New Zealand agriculture. These farm discussion groups work because farmers will openly share knowledge (due to lack of competition) and, they stay together for years, sometimes for decades.
The iteration eventually became Collective Intelligence, where professionals from over 70 industries and professional backgrounds, come together in teams of nine, to evolve themselves and others.
It works.
The bottom-line? Collective Intelligence members become more effective in their professional and personal lives. 
Effective people build effective companies: Quote from Dave Blackwell – CEO of Spidertracks, and Collective Intelligence member for seven years.
I believe people are capable of great things. They just need some help from time to time.

name: Chris Walti
title: Co-Founder / CEO of Mytra
about:
I'm applying two decades of software and hardware engineering experience to the massive challenge of modernizing automation for supply chain and manufacturing industries. The strain on supply chains and manufacturing systems require immediate and disruptive solutions. PLCs are rigid by design and today's "industrial" products are 4x the cost with .25x the capability vs. standard enterprise tools. Most organizations don't have legions of control engineers to roll out needed systems or take on the tech debt. Mytra provides a platform to simply and efficiently solve the most common task in industry - moving and storing material throughout the facility. These non value add tasks employ between 25-75% of the labor for any industrial operation. Mytra develops a novel racking structure providing a 3D grid traversable along all 3 axes, robots to move material within the system, and the software to easily design, operate, and continuously optimize without the need for automation engineers.

Previous to Mytra I created and led Tesla's Mobile Robotics team. We design, develop, build, and deploy robots across Tesla's manufacturing portfolio. The team includes mechanical, electrical, software, controls, perception, manufacturing, and operations experts. We create wheeled mobile robots that serve our factories, and also develop the humanoid Tesla Bot (Optimus).

My professional experiences involve leading engineering teams to design and launch new products, both as an entrepreneur and an "intrapreneur" (within existing companies). They combine hardware and software. The technical challenges/risk and level of responsibility have increased with each role.
notable_achievements: Co-Founder and CEO of Mytra, a company focused on industrial automation with integrated hardware-software solutions; Worked at Tesla driving innovation in mobile robotics and Supercharging; Successfully raised multiple funding rounds totaling $78 million for Mytra

about:
Feyi Ayodele is a healthcare entrepreneur and innovator, recognized for expanding access to personalized cancer prevention, early detection and treatment. Modern Healthcare’s Top Innovator Awards describe her as someone who "thinks outside the box to improve care, achieve measurable results, and contribute to clinical and financial goals."  

Feyi founded CancerIQ in 2014 with a transformational idea: Many of the tools we need to get ahead of cancer already exist; they simply need to be extended beyond the ivory towers of academia. Working closely with leading clinicians in the field, cancer genetics experts, and health system executives, Feyi has led the development of a best-in-class platform that leverages data analytics, AI, genetic testing and other cutting-edge innovations to make precision health more equitable and accessible for all patients. 

Today, CancerIQ is being used in 50+ health systems across the country. The company’s innovative mission is also backed by industry leaders, including Merck Global Health Innovation Fund, Amgen Ventures, and McKesson Ventures. 

CancerIQ’s success has established Feyi as a trusted expert in the field of precision prevention and health equity. She is routinely featured by prominent industry outlets and organizations including Forbes, Modern Healthcare, Health Management Academy, the Association of Cancer Executives, and more. She has also won multiple awards and honors, including those from Modern Healthcare, Chicago Innovation, the Chicago Booth New Venture Challenge, Rock Health, Women Tech Founders and 1871. 

Feyi received both her bachelor’s and MBA from The Wharton School. Prior to CancerIQ, she worked as a management consultant, investor, and investment banker at McKinsey, Actis LLP, and Credit Suisse, respectively.

name: Meghan Conroy
title: Founder
about:
Meghan Conroy, the visionary founder of CaptureProof, has redefined the landscape of medical documentation and analysis through her cutting-edge approach to using visual health technology. She identified a crucial gap in healthcare—the need for more accurate, efficient, and patient-friendly ways to capture and analyze medical data—and has since pioneered the use of visual data to transform patient care and outcomes, particularly in neurology.

Conroy’s early scientific work in utilizing home videos for neurology assessments earned her an Oral Poster Designation at the American Academy of Neurology in 2013, highlighting the untapped potential of visual data in improving diagnostic accuracy. Since then, her influence has only expanded. Meghan has continued to break new ground with the development of CaptureProof, an eClinical Outcomes Assessment (eCOA) tool that allows for asynchronous visual healthcare communication. CaptureProof integrates AI, computer vision, and machine learning to capture near real-time photo and video data for everything from PROs to advanced fall risk assessments. This technology has revolutionized the field of neurology by creating “visual endpoints” in medicine—dynamic data points that offer clinicians new dimensions in tracking patient progress and optimizing treatment plans.

Under Conroy's leadership, CaptureProof has evolved into a leading platform, empowering healthcare providers with AI-driven insights into patient mobility, motor functions, and chronic disease management. Its adoption across multiple specialties and its ability to integrate with various clinical workflows make CaptureProof a critical tool in modern healthcare.

Recent milestones include the platform's application in large-scale clinical trials and real-world evidence generation for neurology and geriatric care. CaptureProof has partnered with global healthcare leaders to tackle some of the most pressing challenges in healthcare, from fall prevention to remote patient monitoring.

In addition to her work with CaptureProof, Conroy is also the founder of brilliantHush, a Clinical Trial Photography Management company, and Unicorn Cashmere, a leading e-tailer of luxury cashmere clothing. She remains an award-winning photographer, having received the Saatchi Award for her evocative work "I am Silent..." Conroy’s multidisciplinary approach to innovation reflects her dedication to transforming how medical data is captured, analyzed, and used to improve patient care and healthcare outcomes worldwide.

name: Kyle Robertson
title: Founder and CEO, Charge⚡Health | Previously Co-Founder and CEO, NarrativeDx (acquired by Press Ganey)
about:
Kyle is an entrepreneur, inventor and investor.

Kyle is the Founder and CEO of Charge Health.  Charge Health provides a mobile social game that helps Chief Nursing Officers build workplace cultures of belonging.  Charge Health fosters positivity and connection by making it easy and fun to support coworkers, which drives improvement in job satisfaction and retention.  Learn more at http://www.chargehealth.co

Kyle was previously the co-founder and CEO of NarrativeDx, the industry leader in healthcare experience analytics. NarrativeDx is utilized by over 80% of US hospitals and health systems, including 14 of the top 20 US News and World Report health systems. Kyle was granted 6 patents for his inventions in natural language processing and artificial intelligence.

NarrativeDx was supported by leading VCs like HealthX Ventures, Cultivation Capital, Summation Health Ventures, ChristianaCare Ventures, The Texas Medical Center Venture Fund, Techstars and Live Oak Venture Partners. Kyle led NarrativeDx through a successful acquisition to the market leader Press Ganey in March 2020.

Prior to founding NarrativeDx, Kyle was a computer engineer for National Instruments, an intellectual property attorney at WilmerHale, and founder and CEO of iCare, the first mobile crowd-funding platform for nonprofits.

Kyle serves as a Board Member for Food Connect, a non-profit focused on alleviating food insecurity. He is also a board member at Lena, the AI Assistant for Patient Care Coordination and BodySpec, the leading provider of DEXA screenings for preventative health.

name: Cory Kidd
title: Partner & Chief Scientist at Strange Ventures | Founder & CEO at Advient Advisors | AI Technology Executive and Product Leader
about:
As a seasoned technology executive and AI expert, I bring over two decades of experience innovating at the intersection of artificial intelligence, psychology, and healthcare. My passion lies in developing accessible, cutting-edge solutions that drive meaningful improvements in patient outcomes.

Most recently, I founded and led Catalia Health, revolutionizing patient care management for chronic conditions through an AI-powered platform that delivered personalized, engaging interactions to support adherence and well-being. Over nearly a decade, I grew Catalia Health into a successful company, securing major clients like Pfizer, Novartis, and Kaiser Permanente, raising $12M from top investors, and garnering significant media recognition. This journey built on my prior experience founding Intuitive Automata and my groundbreaking Ph.D. work at the MIT Media Lab.

Through these roles, I've honed my ability to navigate complex healthcare landscapes and bring together diverse teams to deliver transformative solutions. I'm adept at making advanced technologies accessible to a wide audience, a skill I've leveraged not only in product development but also as a sought-after public speaker and thought leader.

Today, I continue to advise and consult with innovative healthcare technology companies through my role at Sigla Sciences and board positions with Ellipsis Health, Ambit, Silicon Valley Robotics, and others. I'm excited to bring my expertise to new challenges, always with an eye toward creating solutions that are both cutting-edge and human-centered.

If you're working on initiatives that combine AI, healthcare, and real-world impact, I'd love to connect and explore how we might collaborate to drive meaningful change. Please feel free to reach out!

As CEO and Co-founder of Lily AI, I’m proud to be part of the leading AI-powered Product Content Optimization platform that bridges the gap between consumers, merchants, marketers, and machines. At Lily AI, we are transforming advertising and eCommerce by converting nuanced consumer language into precise product understanding, helping consumers navigate millions of products to find the perfect item for their unique context. I am proud to be an immigrant founder who has been on 6 visas in the last 4 years to live my American dream. I am also a Tory Burch Fellow(2019) and hold an MBA from Indian School of Business and Bachelor’s in Economics from Shri Ram College of Commerce (India).

name: Kurtis Minder
title: Building Safer Digital Ecosystems | Purpose-Driven Advisor & Speaker | Successful Entrepreneur | Author of Cyber Recon
about:
My obsession with technology was driven by my parents. My father worked at a flour mill. When I visited his work as a youngster, it shook me. It was hot and loud, with a haze of flour dust in the air. When I visited my mom’s workplace, however, it was clean and quiet, and the coffee machine was within reach. I didn’t understand what my mom did working for the State of Illinois (it was accounting,) but they all had machines on their desks. So, I dug into the technology behind those machines.

Back then, I wasn’t thinking about ransomware, international negotiations, or public policy. I was focused on solving problems—big and small—because I loved the challenge of making something work where others saw impossibility.

Fast forward a few decades and that same love of problem-solving has defined my career. As the founder and CEO of GroupSense, I’ve spent years helping organizations navigate the complex and often dangerous world of cybersecurity. Whether it’s negotiating directly with ransomware threat actors, advising governments on critical infrastructure security, or building tools from scratch, I’ve always approached challenges with a mix of technical depth, empathy, and sheer determination.

My journey has never been conventional. I didn’t enter this field with a pedigree or a perfectly charted plan. Instead, I forged my own path—breaking things, learning quickly, and building solutions that matter. 
Along the way, I’ve been privileged to work with talented teams, influence national security initiatives, and tackle cyber threats that make the headlines.

Now, as I expand my focus to strategic advisory roles, public speaking, and authorship, my mission remains the same: to empower others to navigate the digital world safely and with confidence. I believe the best solutions aren’t just technical—they’re human. And I’m here to bridge that gap.

When I’m not diving deep into cybersecurity challenges, you’ll find me on a motorcycle crossing the country, exploring the outdoors, or tinkering with projects that demand just the right mix of precision and discipline. These moments remind me that the best work comes when we approach life with curiosity, grit, and a sense of purpose.

Let’s connect—whether you’re looking to solve complex problems, share ideas, or collaborate on building a safer digital ecosystem.

name: William Santana Li
title: CEO Knightscope (NASDAQ: KSCP)
about:
William (“Bill”) Santana Li has served as our Chairman and Chief Executive Officer (“CEO”) of Knightscope, Inc. (NASDAQ: KSCP) since April 2013. Mr. Li is an American entrepreneur with over 30 years of experience from working in the global automotive sector and founding and leading a number of startups. From 1990 to 1999, Mr. Li held multiple business and technical positions at Ford Motor Company across four continents.

His positions at Ford ranged from component, systems, and vehicle engineering with the Visteon, Mazda, and Lincoln brands; to business and product strategy on the United States youth market, India, and the emerging markets in Asia-Pacific and South America; as well as the financial turnaround of Ford of Europe. In addition, he was on the “Amazon” team, which established an all-new modular plant in Brazil. Subsequently, he served as Director of Mergers & Acquisitions.

After internally securing $250 million in financing, Mr. Li founded and served as COO of GreenLeaf LLC, a Ford Motor Company subsidiary that became the world’s second largest automotive recycler. Under his leadership, GreenLeaf grew to more than 600 employees, 20 locations worldwide, and annual sales of approximately $150 million. At the age of 28, Bill was the youngest senior executive at Ford Motor Company worldwide.

After successfully establishing GreenLeaf, Mr. Li was recruited by SoftBank Venture Capital to establish and serve as the President and CEO of the Model E Corporation, a newly established automobile manufacturer that focused on the “Subscribe and Drive” model in California. Mr. Li also founded Carbon Motors Corporation in 2003, and as its Chairman and CEO until February 2013, focused it on developing the world’s first purpose-built law enforcement patrol vehicle.

Mr. Li earned a BSEE from Carnegie Mellon University and an MBA from the University of Detroit Mercy.

name: Shahzor Ahmad, Ph.D.
title: Navigating Deep-Tech Frontiers in AI, Cloud, 3D & Digital Transformation
about:
I’m Shahzor, Co-Founder & CEO of Synapsify - a deep-tech consulting firm delivering AI-first, cloud-native solutions for workforce automation, operational agility, and inclusive digital transformation across APAC, MENA, and beyond.

At Synapsify, we combine advanced R&D with agile execution, building award-winning no-code and low-code platforms. Our flagship product, Synapsivate (https://synapsivate.com/hrm), features an AI scheduling engine deployed for Yue Hwa Chinese Products under Singapore’s IMDA Open Innovation Platform. We’ve also collaborated on developing VR-ready banking solutions (Fasset and Allied Bank Limited), AI+AR tools for neurodiverse learning (National Council of Social Service, Singapore, and Thye Hua Kwan Moral Charities, Singapore) (https://synapsiverse.com/juniors), and accounting automation platform Ledgerate (https://ledgerate.com/) - which cleans up sales chaos without code (Accounts Inc International, Singapore).

Alongside our consulting practice, we incubate and operate a portfolio of next-gen platforms spanning synthetic data (https://altroverse.ai/), emotive voice + avatar tech (https://neuralcords.ai/), and serverless AI infrastructure (https://neuralhive.ai/) - designed to scale innovation across industries.

As CEO, I lead Synapsify’s strategy, product vision, and cross-border growth - driving high-impact services across AI, cloud, and 3D, while scaling a complementary suite of platforms for automation and enterprise tech. I’ve proudly represented Synapsify at the Silk Road Int’l Expo (China), Tech Week Singapore, and NCSS Social Service Summit (Singapore).

We're a founder-led, fast-moving team headquartered in Pakistan - registered with Pakistan Software Export Board (PSEB) and the Rawalpindi Chamber of Commerce & Industry (RCCI) - building future-ready platforms to solve today’s hardest digital challenges.

Let’s connect and collaborate on what’s next.

name: Christopher Walker
title: Founder and CTO Marvelous AI
about:
Christopher Walker is a hands-on player-coach with an extensive knowledge of web- and language-data technologies. Working with diverse teams of engineers, linguists and analysts, Christopher has often managed dozens of language technology projects in parallel, for tasks as varied as speech detection in Dari, speaker identification in Farsi, information retrieval in Chinese and transliteration of Berber Tifinagh.

In 2018, he co-founded MarvelousAI, an early stage startup building an augmented analytics platform to provide actionable insights regarding online narratives by combining the power of human-in-the-loop learning with the latest in natural language processing, computational linguistics, and machine learning. MarvelousAI is focused on how messaging spreads in online media, both negatively (propaganda) and positively (truth-based messages); which narratives persist over time; and the impact they have on overall discourse about a topic. 

In 2012, he co-founded idibon and built a state-of-the-art natural language processing API to serve enterprise clients in the management of large-scale data, both structured and unstructured.  Prior, he brought his Silicon Valley experience to bear modernizing the software group at the Linguistic Data Consortium, the world’s largest collection of language data covering machine translation, speech recognition and text mining. Before that, he was responsible for language data and evaluation at the web search startup Powerset--leveraging not only traditional and crowd-sourced methods of corpus creation, but also hybrid methods that incorporated the HLT under development. Responsible for all NLP evaluation at Powerset, he developed a unique crowd-driven methodology for the evaluation of complex semantic graphs. Later, when Powerset was acquired by Bing, Christopher implemented a hybrid process for review summarization that layered PARC's NLP parsing technology with standard statistical methods.

I am currently an Assistant Professor at Michigan Tech University's Department of Humanities. 

My scholarship, inclusive of research, teaching, and community engagement and organizing, centers around humanistic perspectives on resistance and activism. My research and writing today is focusing on the stories of "new" activism and resistance, that is the journeys of everyday people finding ways to resist in the current American political environment, particularly since the 2024 presidential election. I also organize a grassroots social movement organization, and teach activism and resistance (as well as culture, communication, and media) at Michigan Tech University.

name: Kristian Hammond
title: Professor of Computer Science at Northwestern University / Director of The Center for Advancing Safety of Machine Intelligence (CASMI)
about:
Kristian Hammond is the Bill and Cathy Osborn Professor of Computer Science at Northwestern University and the co-founder of the Artificial Intelligence company Narrative Science (acquired by Salesforce in 2021). He has spent most of his career focused on the problem of making machines smarter. His research is aimed at bridging the human/machine communication gap between the data we gather and the information that is locked within it. 

Since the fall of 2016, he has been the faculty lead of Northwestern’s CS + X initiative, exploring how computational thinking can be used to transform fields such as the law, medicine, and education. He also directs Northwestern’s Master of Science in Artificial Intelligence (MSAI) as well as the Center for Advancing Safety of Machine Intelligence (CASMI). In January of 2023, he was named a Fellow of the Association for the Advancement of Artificial Intelligence (AAAI). 

He believes in humanizing computers with the aim of stopping the process of mechanizing people. Kris received his PhD from Yale.
